A police source has confirmed that Calvin November 58, the father of six-year-old Shasha-Lee November, who has gone missing, has been arrested. November was arrested on Thursday afternoon, a day after a vigil was held for his daughter. He was arrested for the illegal possession of ammunition and drugs. November made a brief appearance in the Athlone Magistrate's Court on Friday morning. Shasha-Lee went missing in 2015. She was last seen playing outside her home in Groenall Walk in Hanover Park. The police have to date had no new developments in the case. 